to add another source of randomness, define/implement the below.


#typedef xxxxx reason_t ------ A reasonable datatype for dice rolling.
#define reason_format xxxxx -- The fprintf format specifier for reason_t.

void init_random(void) ------- Setup random number generator.
void remove_random(void) ----- De-init random number generator.

reason_t random_number(void) - Random number bounded by the underlying datatype and > 0.
As of this writing, the output of random_number gets mod divided with reason_t faces.

reason_t strtoreason(char *const str, char **e_str) - Convert str to reason_t datatype.
e_str points to the first unrecognized char or the '\0' at the end of the string.


